-- Bank Pocztowy May Delay Share Sale Until Second Half of 2011, Rp.pl Says
-- B y   M o n i k a   R o z l a l
-- 2010-10-12T06:01:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/bank-pocztowy-may-delay-share-sale-until-second-half-of-2011-rp-pl-says.html
Bank Pocztowy SA wants to delay its
initial public offering by about six months after publishing
2011 first-half results,  rp.pl  reported, citing Deputy Chief
Executive Officer Szymon Midera.  The Polish state-controlled lender earlier planned to
publish a prospectus in July 2011, Pocztowy said on its website.
The bank wants to raise as much as 350 million zloty ($122
million) and plans to pick an adviser for the IPO by the end of
the year, rp.pl added.  Poczta Polska SA, the Polish state-owned postal company,
owns 75 percent of Pocztowy, and  PKO Bank Polski SA , Polandâ€™s
biggest bank, owns 25 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
